+## Document Pros and Cons
+
+When a plan picks between alternatives (library, architecture pattern, data structure, approach), include a brief pros/cons/why block:
+
+> **Pros:** [advantages]
+> **Cons:** [disadvantages]
+> **Why we chose this:** [reasoning]
+
+Proportional to decision weight — a minor choice gets one line each, a major choice gets a paragraph. If one option clearly dominates, auto-select and state why.
+
+## Prose Quality
+
+All non-code text in the plan (descriptions, context, rationale) must read like a person wrote it. Apply the `humanizer` skill patterns — strip AI-isms as you write, don't produce slop then clean it up.
+
+**Applies to:** Goal statement, Architecture summary, task descriptions, explanatory notes.
+**Does NOT apply to:** code blocks, file paths, commands, expected output, step labels.
+
+Watch for: significance inflation, promotional language, copula avoidance ("serves as" instead of "is"), superficial -ing phrases, filler, generic conclusions, rule-of-three padding. Be direct and specific.
+
